com.smoothcsv.core.macro.api

Interface Range


  • public interface Range
    The representation of a cell (or cells) on your csv sheet.

    • Method Summary

      Make this range the active range.

      • offset

        Range offset(int rowOffset,
             int columnOffset)
        Returns a new range that is offset from this range by the given number of rows and columns (which can be negative). The new range will be the same size as the original range.
        Parameters:
        rowOffset - number of rows down from the range's top-left cell; negative values represent rows up from the range's top-left cell
        columnOffset - number of columns right from the range's top-left cell; negative values represent columns left from the range's top-left cell
        Returns:
        the range for chaining

      • offset

        Range offset(int rowOffset,
             int columnOffset,
             int numRows,
             int numColumns)
        Returns a new range that is relative to the current range, whose upper left point is offset from the current range by the given rows and columns, and with the given height and width in cells.
        Parameters:
        rowOffset - number of rows down from the range's top-left cell; negative values represent rows up from the range's top-left cell
        columnOffset - number of columns right from the range's top-left cell; negative values represent columns left from the range's top-left cell
        numRows - the height in rows of the new range
        numColumns - the width in columns of the new range
        Returns:
        the range for chaining
